description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a dynamic and innovative individual to do things differently in supporting and leading elements of the ‘Move More, Eat Well’ agenda and other areas across Cardiff and the Vale of Glamorgan, working as a Senior Public Health Practitioner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is based within the Cardiff and Vale of Glamorgan Local Public Health Team working across Cardiff and Vale University Health Board and reporting to its Executive Director for Public Health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will require excellent communication and team working skills to enable them to work together with a wide range of partner organisations, across Public Services Boards (aligned to the Wellbeing of Future Generations (Wales) Act), and through the Regional Partnership Board (aligned to the Social Services and Wellbeing (Wales) Act). They will work with partners to plan, develop and deliver programmes and initiatives at both strategic and operational levels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Lauren Idowu, on 02921 836505 or lauren.idowu@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cardiff and Vale University Local Health Board is situated in the vibrant easily accessible capital of Wales which combines the best of city life, coast and countryside.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 15th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Lauren Idowu&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Principal Health Promotion Specialist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: lauren.idowu@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 02921 836505&lt;/p&gt;
